      Why are garage doors so expensive?
      Supply chain disruptions: The COVID-19 pandemic has caused disruptions in global supply chains, which has led to shortages of certain materials and parts needed for manufacturing garage doors. This has resulted in increased costs for manufacturers, which are then passed on to consumers.20 Mar 2023

      What sizes are garage doors?
      The standard garage door width and height can vary by where you live, but is usually:
      • 8 feet wide by 7 feet tall, or 9 feet wide by 7 feet tall for a single car garage door.
      • 16 feet by 7 feet for a double garage door.

      How wide is a standard garage door in meters?
      As a general rule of thumb, the standard garage door dimensions are: Single door: 7ft (2,134 mm) x 7ft (2,134 mm) Double door: 14ft (4,267 mm) x 7ft (2,134 mm) or 16ft (4,877 mm) x 7ft (2,134 mm)10 May 2023

      How much is it to research a garage door?
      Unlike the sheet metal door, the garage door is not a default blueprint. Once you find one, it'll cost 75 scrap to research and then require a level 1 workbench to craft.26 Oct 2017
